The morning sun spills golden rays,
Across the hills, the fields ablaze;
The world awakens with a sigh,
In harmony with earth and sky.

Each creature stirs, each flower stuns,
A celebration has begun;
In this purity, life shines bright,
Guided by natureâ€™s loving light.

- Richard Jefferies
